parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure in Wet Weather Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system in wet weather conditions can cause the loss of power steering, braking ability, and illumination of the battery and brake indicator lights, leading to increased risk of accidents and loss of control.
symptoms: and illumination of the battery and brake indicator lights
loud screeching sound from under the hood
reduced power to headlights and dashlights
and major difficulty turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ECS light turns on while driving
loss of control of the steering wheel
and the steering wheel becomes hard to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The cruise control fails to disengage when the brakes are depressed
and the airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of power steering, leading to reduced control and increased risk of accidents, as well as intermittent shutdowns, which can leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the power steering system can cause the loss of power steering, leading to reduced control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: and increased effort required to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent shutdowns can leave the driver stranded, causing inconvenience and potential safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Door Lock and Window Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the door locks and window can cause inconvenience, compromise vehicle security, and potentially lead to safety issues if the driver is unable to exit the vehicle quickly in an emergency situation.
symptoms: the door locks do not respond to the remote or lock button
the door locks affect all doors except the tailgate
the driver's window has difficulty going down sporadically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop lamp switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, it can also prevent the shifter from moving out of park, leaving the vehicle stranded.
